Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

Hi, this implementation does not work when more than one vnf is definied in the request, for example, if request is like this:

  "requestDetails": {
    "requestParameters": {
      "userParams": [
        {
          "service": {
            "resources": {
              "vnfs": [
                {
                  "instanceName": "vnf1",
                  "instanceParams": [
                    {
                      "k1": "v1",
                      "k2": "v2"
                    }, 
                    {
                       "k3": "v3"
                    }
                  ]           
                }
                {
                	"instanceName": "vnf2",
                  	"instanceParams": [
                    {
                      "key4": "v4",
                      "key5": "v5"                    
                    }]}]}}}]}}

We have two vnfs defined. 

Now, the line of code: 
GenericVnf vnf = extractPojosForBB.extractByKey(execution, ResourceKey.GENERIC_VNF_ID)

is supposed to choose one specific vnf, and we are going to prepare request to CDS for this one vnf. 
Your implementation puts all instanceParams values from all vnf to ConfigAssignPropertiesForVnf object. 
You should choose instanceParams that belongs to specific vnf that is chosen to be sent do CDS.
